reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love my WLIVE Wide Dresser! The instructions were incredibly clear and helpful, making the assembly process a breeze. Its light and easy-to-move design is perfect for rearranging my space whenever I feel like it. Despite its affordability, the dresser looks fantastic and adds a chic touch to my room. I'm thrilled with the value it offers. It's not just a dresser; it's an elegant addition to my home that meets all my storage needs. Highly recommend it to anyone looking for a stylish, functional, and affordable furniture piece!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for the price
reviews.reviewText: For as cheap as this dresser is, I quite like it. It looks pretty nice and stores everything I want it to. I really like the extra depth compared to most other cheap dressers on Amazon, which was why I chose this particular model. It's a bit wobbly side-to-side, but still reasonably sturdy if you don't push on it. I put several heavy books and other items on top and it seems to handle those, along with the drawers pretty full, just fine.Assembly is pretty easy. I only glanced at the instructions a few times but they are fine. The only thing to look out for - make sure you get the two side pieces correct! They seemed reversible to me at first, so I just grabbed one and started putting it together only to later realize they are NOT reversible and I got them backwards! Double check you have the left and right side pieces correct before assembling, and everything else will go smooth and easy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Shorter than expected
reviews.reviewText: Only took about an hour to put together and was very easy just a lot of tiny pieces and parts. A little wobbly but sturdy enough to hold my gecko’s enclosure so it isn’t horrible. Biggest “problem” or downside I would say is that it’s shorter than expected and barely reaches my bed, which has a box spring and only a tiny lift. Short but cute!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price!
reviews.reviewText: So I bought two of these. I have absolutely no handyman skills but this was pretty easy to assemble since it came with the wrench/ screwdriver needed. It did take about an hour for each but once completed, they look great and are able to hold a lot of clothes, kids clothes specifically!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It was 30% off when I bought it so it was $73 a piece. I bought two because I needed the extra storage and I really like how they look. This turned out to be an amazing bang for my buck! Super lightweight but well made with sturdy compartments. The top is wood but the drawer fronts are fabric. The fabric that looks like wood is reinforced or something so it’s a little more solid than the rest of the drawer. Makes it look more realistic though. I wouldn’t be able to tell it was fabric until I touched it. I highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought 2 night stands and a chest of drawers. The night stands were straight forward with easy to follow instructions but the chest had hard to follow instructions with no detail on how to put it together. Just some pictures that were not clear at all and the hardware nrs didn't match the pictures. Very confusing. took 2 hrs to put it together. Looked good and pretty sturdy when it was done but I wouldn't go through that again.
